{"article_id":"UUN5WZdBYtfHjg50","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"North Korea tested an intercontinental ballistic missile","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"that can hit most of the US mainland","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"on July 28 .","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"It detonated its largest nuclear bomb yet on September 3 .","depth":3},{"id":4,"text":"And it also twice launched missiles over Japan this year , most recently on September 15 local time .","depth":3},{"id":5,"text":"North Korea continues to expressly defy the wishes of the United States and the international community","depth":3},{"id":6,"text":"by carrying out provocative actions .","depth":3},{"id":7,"text":"Now it is up to Trump to decide how to respond","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"- and he is left with very bad options","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"to do so .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"On August 8 , Trump said","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"the US would unleash \" fire and fury \" on North Korea","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"if it continued to threaten America .","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"But the administration prefers to pursue its strategy of diplomacy and economic pressure","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"- for now .","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"Still , Trump is the next US leader","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"to struggle with how to handle North Korea after its most recent provocation .","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"Presidents from Bill Clinton to Barack Obama tried different approaches","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"to deal with the Hermit Kingdom ,","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"such as diplomatic engagement ,","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"labeling it a state sponsor of terror ,","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"or simply ignoring it in hopes","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"that the regime would collapse on its own .","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"None of those approaches worked","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"as the regimes of Kim and his father","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"- and North Korea ' s nuclear and ballistic missile programs more generally -","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"outlasted them all .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"\" US policy toward North Korea has been unsuccessful for a couple of decades , \"","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"Sheena Greitens , a North Korea expert at the University of Missouri , said in an interview .","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"\" We ' re seeing the consequences of that now . \"","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"With Pyongyang successfully testing a missile","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"capable of hitting the mainland ,","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"Trump is tasked with trying to find some way","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"to keep the danger from getting even worse .","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"However , the options","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"he has available to him","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"are broadly the same as the ones","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"his predecessors had :","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"military strikes , diplomacy , or economic sanctions .","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"The military option would entail a \" surgical strike \" on North Korea ' s nuclear sites","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"to take out the country ' s missiles as well as the country ' s political leadership ,","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"including Kim Jong Un .","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"The problem is that North Korea would be certain to hit back hard ,","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"using its own large artillery arsenal","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"to strike at America ' s allies , South Korea , and Japan .","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"That would likely kill tens or even hundreds of thousands of people","depth":13},{"id":46,"text":"- including US troops","depth":14},{"id":47,"text":"stationed in both countries -","depth":14},{"id":48,"text":"even before nuclear weapons were dropped .","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"The diplomatic option would see the US try to come to some sort of agreement with North Korea","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"to either give up its programs","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"or , at a minimum , freeze their development .","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"Over the past few decades , though , North Korea has shown no desire to follow any agreements ,","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"consistently breaking accords with the US and its partners","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"and covertly advancing its nuclear weapons and missile efforts .","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"And the sanctions would be meant to impose so much economic pain on Pyongyang","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"that it would conclude","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"that the costs","depth":14},{"id":58,"text":"of continuing the programs are too high .","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"But many items","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"the country wants and needs ,","depth":14},{"id":61,"text":"like weapons and fuel ,","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"are already highly sanctioned by the US .","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"North Korea hasn ' t changed its course .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"So , the options for Trump are poor and fraught with risk .","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"\" There are no silver bullet solutions , \"","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"James Miller , the top Pentagon policy official from 2012 to 2014 , told me .","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"In some ways , that means","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"the bigger and more immediate question is whether Trump can avoid taking steps","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"that make the problem worse .","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"The options","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"for dealing with North Korea all have huge downsides","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"As Greitens told me ,","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"there are basically three broad options","depth":15},{"id":74,"text":"Trump can choose from :","depth":15},{"id":75,"text":"1 ) military strikes ; 2 ) diplomacy ;","depth":15},{"id":76,"text":"or 3 ) economic sanctions .","depth":15},{"id":77,"text":"But here ' s the rub :","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"option one is incredibly dangerous ,","depth":14},{"id":79,"text":"and options two and three have a mixed track record at best .","depth":14},{"id":80,"text":"First , the military option .","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"The last thing","depth":15},{"id":82,"text":"Defense Secretary James Mattis wants","depth":15},{"id":83,"text":"is a war with North Korea .","depth":14},{"id":84,"text":"`` A conflict in North Korea ,","depth":15},{"id":85,"text":"\"","depth":16},{"id":86,"text":"he told CBS ' s John Dickerson on May 28 ,","depth":16},{"id":87,"text":"\" would be probably the worst kind of fighting in most people 's lifetimes . ''","depth":14},{"id":88,"text":"Gen. Vincent Brooks ,","depth":14},{"id":89,"text":"who commands US troops in South Korea ,","depth":14},{"id":90,"text":"thinks","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"that tensions are high between the North and South ,","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"as the only thing","depth":16},{"id":93,"text":"keeping both sides from fighting","depth":16},{"id":94,"text":"is \" self-restraint. \"","depth":15},{"id":95,"text":"In other words , there ' s nothing really keeping the two countries from warring","depth":15},{"id":96,"text":"except a massive provocation or miscalculation .","depth":15},{"id":97,"text":"That ' s not only a problem for the Koreas ,","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"but also for America .","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"Around 23,500 US troops are stationed in South Korea .","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"Many of them are within reach of North Korea ' s artillery .","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"And ,","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"should a war break out ,","depth":14},{"id":103,"text":"many would be killed","depth":14},{"id":104,"text":"as they would be considered top targets by the North .","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"If the US is worried","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"North Korea might make the first move , though ,","depth":14},{"id":107,"text":"it could launch a preemptive surgical strike on North Korea .","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"It would certainly do damage to the country ' s missile and nuclear programs .","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"But North Korea would retaliate ,","depth":14},{"id":110,"text":"imperiling the safety of US allies South Korea and Japan .","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"Pyongyang has the world ' s largest artillery arsenal at its disposal , with around 8,000 rocket launchers and artillery cannons on its side of the demilitarized zone between the North and South ,","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"and it could use that arsenal","depth":14},{"id":113,"text":"to strike the major capital of Seoul .","depth":14},{"id":114,"text":"It could also use its short-range missiles","depth":14},{"id":115,"text":"to strike Tokyo and other large Japanese urban areas , some of them with only about a 10-minute warning .","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"But a fight between the North and South would be bad enough .","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"Simulations of a large-scale artillery fight produce pretty bleak results .","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"One war game","depth":17},{"id":119,"text":"convened by the Atlantic back in 2005","depth":17},{"id":120,"text":"predicted","depth":16},{"id":121,"text":"that a North Korean attack would kill 100,000 people in Seoul in the first few days alone .","depth":15},{"id":122,"text":"Others put the estimate even higher .","depth":15},{"id":123,"text":"A war game","depth":18},{"id":124,"text":"mentioned by the National Interest","depth":18},{"id":125,"text":"predicted","depth":17},{"id":126,"text":"Seoul could \" be hit by over half-a-million shells in under an hour. \"","depth":16},{"id":127,"text":"Those results don ' t bode well for one of Washington ' s closest allies , or for the 25.6 million people","depth":14},{"id":128,"text":"living in Seoul .","depth":14},{"id":129,"text":"None of this even factors in the large-scale refugee crisis","depth":14},{"id":130,"text":"that a war would create ,","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"where millions would flock north to China","depth":14},{"id":132,"text":"as their homes and livelihoods are ravaged by war .","depth":14},{"id":133,"text":"That ' s something China expressly does not want .","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"Beijing prioritizes stability on the peninsula ,","depth":13},{"id":135,"text":"and it helps explain why it has been so unwilling to alter the status quo in North Korea .","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"Any change ,","depth":14},{"id":137,"text":"China fears ,","depth":14},{"id":138,"text":"may lead to problems for the Chinese government down the road .","depth":13},{"id":139,"text":"Here ' s the end result ,","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"according to my colleague Zack Beauchamp :","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"\" Given North Korea ' s massive conventional military and unknown number of nuclear weapons ,","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"conflict on the Korean Peninsula would cost hundreds of thousands , if not millions , of lives . \"","depth":10},{"id":143,"text":"So a surgical strike may have risks","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"because of what North Korea might do .","depth":11},{"id":145,"text":"It ' s also a risk","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"because the strike itself may not work","depth":13},{"id":147,"text":"as planned .","depth":13},{"id":148,"text":"The reason for that is many of North Korea ' s nuclear sites are underground or in caves .","depth":12},{"id":149,"text":"Plus , the US and its partners are unsure","depth":14},{"id":150,"text":"where many of the dozens of missiles","depth":16},{"id":151,"text":"that would carry a nuclear weapon","depth":16},{"id":152,"text":"are .","depth":15},{"id":153,"text":"Some are hidden away","depth":14},{"id":154,"text":"and others are on mobile launchers","depth":15},{"id":155,"text":"that could be moved","depth":16},{"id":156,"text":"if North Korea sensed","depth":17},{"id":157,"text":"an attack was coming .","depth":17},{"id":158,"text":"Either way , special operations forces would likely be on the ground in North Korea ,","depth":10},{"id":159,"text":"conducting risky military maneuvers","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"- putting themselves in harm ' s way .","depth":11},{"id":161,"text":"But so far , the Trump administration has avoided military options .","depth":9},{"id":162,"text":"It would prefer to solve the crisis diplomatically ,","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"according to an August 13 op-ed piece by Mattis and Secretary of State Rex Tillerson .","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"\" While diplomacy is our preferred means","depth":15},{"id":165,"text":"of changing North Korea ' s course of action ,","depth":15},{"id":166,"text":"it is backed by military options , \"","depth":14},{"id":167,"text":"they wrote .","depth":13},{"id":168,"text":"\" The US is willing to negotiate with Pyongyang .","depth":13},{"id":169,"text":"But","depth":15},{"id":170,"text":"given the long record of North Korea ' s dishonesty in negotiations and repeated violations of international agreements ,","depth":15},{"id":171,"text":"it is incumbent upon the regime to signal its desire","depth":15},{"id":172,"text":"to negotiate in good faith . \"","depth":15},{"id":173,"text":"Clearly , that approach has yet to work .","depth":11},{"id":174,"text":"But to be fair ,","depth":12},{"id":175,"text":"its hasn ' t worked for past administrations , either .","depth":12},{"id":176,"text":"America and others have tried to come to some sort of diplomatic , negotiated agreement with North Korea over its programs since 1985 ,","depth":10},{"id":177,"text":"according to the Arms Control Association .","depth":10},{"id":178,"text":"They got really close twice .","depth":10},{"id":179,"text":"In 1994 , the US and North Korea signed the Agreed Framework ,","depth":12},{"id":180,"text":"in which the North agreed to freeze its plutonium weapons program in exchange for two proliferation-resistant nuclear power reactors and fuel oil from the United States .","depth":12},{"id":181,"text":"However , the agreement collapsed in 2002 ,","depth":14},{"id":182,"text":"and by January 2003 the North had resumed its nuclear program .","depth":14},{"id":183,"text":"Then in August 2003 , the international community launched the so-called \" Six Party Talks , \"","depth":15},{"id":184,"text":"which were designed to get North Korea to halt its nuclear program through negotiations with five other countries :","depth":16},{"id":185,"text":"China , the United States , South Korea , Japan , and Russia .","depth":16},{"id":186,"text":"In September 2005 , it looked like the talks might work","depth":15},{"id":187,"text":"- North Korea formally agreed to abandon \" all nuclear weapons and existing nuclear programs \" in exchange for energy assistance from the other countries .","depth":15},{"id":188,"text":"But in 2009 , amid disagreements over technical details","depth":15},{"id":189,"text":"related to verification ,","depth":15},{"id":190,"text":"North Korea walked out on the talks .","depth":14},{"id":191,"text":"It says","depth":16},{"id":192,"text":"it will never return to the negotiations","depth":16},{"id":193,"text":"and maintains","depth":16},{"id":194,"text":"that it is no longer bound by their agreements .","depth":16},{"id":195,"text":"And it has been ramping up its nuclear and ballistic missile programs ever since .","depth":14},{"id":196,"text":"Kelsey Davenport , a North Korea expert at the Arms Control Association , thinks","depth":15},{"id":197,"text":"diplomacy has the best chance of success ,","depth":15},{"id":198,"text":"but notes","depth":15},{"id":199,"text":"that the cost for the US would be high .","depth":15},{"id":200,"text":"\" That will require the United States to put something on the table","depth":15},{"id":201,"text":"that North Korea wants , perhaps a reduction in US-South Korean military exercises , \"","depth":15},{"id":202,"text":"she said .","depth":14},{"id":203,"text":"South Korea ,","depth":15},{"id":204,"text":"which relies on US security backing","depth":16},{"id":205,"text":"to protect it from China and North Korea ,","depth":16},{"id":206,"text":"would worry about America ' s commitment to it","depth":14},{"id":207,"text":"if that trade were made .","depth":13},{"id":208,"text":"South Korea ' s president , Moon Jae In , has sought a less hawkish approach to North Korea ,","depth":12},{"id":209,"text":"preferring tougher sanctions instead of military maneuvers .","depth":12},{"id":210,"text":"Trump is stuck with the same weak hand","depth":12},{"id":211,"text":"to respond to North Korea","depth":12},{"id":212,"text":"- but North Korea ' s hand got stronger after the ICBM test","depth":11},{"id":213,"text":"Sanctions tend to work much better","depth":13},{"id":214,"text":"before a country obtains what it wants ,","depth":13},{"id":215,"text":"Greitens noted .","depth":12},{"id":216,"text":"In this case , North Korea achieved a big step toward its goal","depth":12},{"id":217,"text":"of having a missile","depth":13},{"id":218,"text":"that can carry a nuclear weapon to America ' s largest cities .","depth":13},{"id":219,"text":"It ' s going to be hard at this point to use sanctions","depth":12},{"id":220,"text":"to change North Korea ' s behavior","depth":12},{"id":221,"text":"when Pyongyang feels like","depth":12},{"id":222,"text":"it is so close to the finish line .","depth":12},{"id":223,"text":"And it ' s not like North Korea sanctions are a new idea .","depth":9},{"id":224,"text":"In fact , sanctions have already been placed on key items","depth":12},{"id":225,"text":"being imported or exported by North Korea :","depth":12},{"id":226,"text":"weaponry big and small ; coal , minerals , and fuel ; luxury goods like yachts ; funding for its missile and nuclear programs ; and even a ban on travel into UN member states for those","depth":12},{"id":227,"text":"who work on the country ' s nuclear program .","depth":12},{"id":228,"text":"On September 11 , the United Nations passed its harshest sanctions package","depth":14},{"id":229,"text":"it ' s ever adopted","depth":14},{"id":230,"text":"against North Korea ,","depth":13},{"id":231,"text":"which includes banning textiles exports and capping shipments of crude oil into the country .","depth":12},{"id":232,"text":"But even then North Korea continues to defy international pressure","depth":12},{"id":233,"text":"by improving its program .","depth":12},{"id":234,"text":"There are also some other maneuvers","depth":9},{"id":235,"text":"Trump could take .","depth":9},{"id":236,"text":"He could try to increase the cyber program","depth":11},{"id":237,"text":"meant to sabotage North Korea ' s missile launches within their first few seconds ,","depth":12},{"id":238,"text":"which the Obama administration pioneered .","depth":12},{"id":239,"text":"Trump could also continue to send more aircraft carriers off the coast of the peninsula as a show of force ,","depth":12},{"id":240,"text":"hoping to intimidate North Korea into stopping their tests .","depth":12},{"id":241,"text":"Or , he could decide to just accept","depth":13},{"id":242,"text":"that North Korea is a nuclear power with the ability","depth":14},{"id":243,"text":"to strike America .","depth":14},{"id":244,"text":"After doing so ,","depth":14},{"id":245,"text":"the US and its partners would seek to contain North Korea ' s nuclear ambitions","depth":15},{"id":246,"text":"and deter an attack","depth":16},{"id":247,"text":"launched from Pyongyang .","depth":16},{"id":248,"text":"But accepting North Korea ' s programs","depth":15},{"id":249,"text":"as they are","depth":15},{"id":250,"text":"is likely the least palatable for the tough-talking Trump .","depth":14},{"id":251,"text":"So , the president is stuck with the same weak hand","depth":11},{"id":252,"text":"to respond to North Korea","depth":11},{"id":253,"text":"- but North Korea ' s hand got stronger after the ICBM and nuclear weapon tests .","depth":10},{"id":254,"text":"It ' s no wonder , then ,","depth":8},{"id":255,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":256,"text":"Trump tried something different","depth":10},{"id":257,"text":"by relying on China","depth":12},{"id":258,"text":"to solve the problem","depth":12},{"id":259,"text":"- even if it didn ' t work .","depth":11},{"id":260,"text":"Trump ' s reliance on China","depth":9},{"id":261,"text":"to handle North Korea","depth":9},{"id":262,"text":"was unlikely to work","depth":8},{"id":263,"text":"Trump ' s plan was to get China to make North Korea halt its missile and nuclear programs .","depth":10},{"id":264,"text":"But Kelly Magsamen , a top Asia Pentagon official in the Obama administration , never thought","depth":12},{"id":265,"text":"that was a good idea .","depth":12},{"id":266,"text":"\" President Trump was foolish to outsource his North Korea strategy to China , \"","depth":13},{"id":267,"text":"she said in an interview .","depth":13},{"id":268,"text":"\" China can certainly play a major role ,","depth":14},{"id":269,"text":"but they don ' t share our interests .","depth":14},{"id":270,"text":"It takes more than one summit and a few tweets","depth":14},{"id":271,"text":"to address the North Korea challenge . \"","depth":14},{"id":272,"text":"China ' s failure","depth":13},{"id":273,"text":"to deliver","depth":13},{"id":274,"text":"was evident back in April","depth":12},{"id":275,"text":"when new data showed","depth":12},{"id":276,"text":"its trade with North Korea had increased by 37.4 percent in the first quarter of 2017 .","depth":12},{"id":277,"text":"North Korea ' s economy is almost entirely dependent on China ,","depth":14},{"id":278,"text":"with Beijing providing Pyongyang with food , fuel , and machinery .","depth":14},{"id":279,"text":"Had China cut that off ,","depth":14},{"id":280,"text":"North Korea would ' ve been in trouble .","depth":14},{"id":281,"text":"But , clearly , the opposite happened .","depth":12},{"id":282,"text":"Trump himself seems to realize now","depth":14},{"id":283,"text":"that China is unwilling to do America ' s bidding on North Korea ,","depth":14},{"id":284,"text":"per his tweet on July 5 .","depth":13},{"id":285,"text":"Trade between China and North Korea grew almost 40 % in the first quarter .","depth":13},{"id":286,"text":"So much for China working with us","depth":15},{"id":287,"text":"- but we had to give it a try !","depth":15},{"id":288,"text":"- Donald J. Trump","depth":16},{"id":289,"text":"( @ realDonaldTrump )","depth":16},{"id":290,"text":"July 5 , 2017","depth":15},{"id":291,"text":"That was a surprising turnaround for Trump ,","depth":11},{"id":292,"text":"especially after he felt","depth":12},{"id":293,"text":"he and Xi came to an understanding on North Korea during their Mar-a-Lago summit back in April .","depth":12},{"id":294,"text":"Then again , Trump promised to be much tougher on China during the campaign ,","depth":13},{"id":295,"text":"claiming","depth":14},{"id":296,"text":"he would deem it a currency manipulator on his first day in office .","depth":14},{"id":297,"text":"He later changed his mind on that .","depth":12},{"id":298,"text":"So , Trump decided to scrap the China plan ,","depth":12},{"id":299,"text":"and now he has to decide what the new course of action will be .","depth":12},{"id":300,"text":"Trump has sold himself as a dealmaker of unparalleled skill ,","depth":11},{"id":301,"text":"and it 's possible he ' ll come up with something creative and new .","depth":11},{"id":302,"text":"It ' s more likely that he ' ll find himself in the same bind as his predecessors .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":605,"left":307,"right":604,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":307,"left":305,"right":306,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":305,"left":304,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":304,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":306,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":604,"left":308,"right":603,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent"